# Cross-Site Scripting (XSS)

> A client-side injection attack where malicious scripts are injected into trusted websites.

---

## 🔍 Types of XSS

### 1. Reflected XSS
- Script is reflected off the web server
- Not stored, only triggered when victim clicks malicious link
- **Example:**
```
https://site.com/search?q=<script>alert(1)</script>
```

### 2. Stored XSS
- Malicious script is permanently stored on the server (DB, logs, comments)
- Every user who visits the page gets attacked
- **Example:** Comment box, profile bio, username

### 3. DOM-Based XSS
- Vulnerability exists in client-side JavaScript
- No server interaction needed
- **Example:**
```javascript
document.innerHTML = location.hash
```

